theorem
(for K being  Fanoian Field holds (for n,i being Nat holds (for M1 being (Matrix of n,K) holds ((M1 is  antisymmetric & i in ( Seg n )) implies ( M1 * (i,i) ) = ( 0. K )))))
proof
let K being  Fanoian Field;
let n;
let i;
let M1 being (Matrix of n,K);
assume that
A1: M1 is  antisymmetric
and
A2: i in ( Seg n );
A3: ( M1 @ ) = ( - M1 ) by A1,CKB39:def 1;
( Indices M1 ) = [: ( Seg n ),( Seg n ) :] by MATRIX_1:24;
then A4: [ i,i ] in ( Indices M1 ) by A2,ZFMISC_1:87;
then ( ( M1 @ ) * (i,i) ) = ( M1 * (i,i) ) by MATRIX_1:def 6;
then ( M1 * (i,i) ) = ( - ( M1 * (i,i) ) ) by A4,A3,MATRIX_3:def 2;
then ( ( M1 * (i,i) ) + ( M1 * (i,i) ) ) = ( 0. K ) by RLVECT_1:5;
then ( ( ( 1_ K ) * ( M1 * (i,i) ) ) + ( M1 * (i,i) ) ) = ( 0. K ) by VECTSP_1:def 8;
then ( ( ( 1_ K ) * ( M1 * (i,i) ) ) + ( ( 1_ K ) * ( M1 * (i,i) ) ) ) = ( 0. K ) by VECTSP_1:def 8;
then (( ( 1_ K ) + ( 1_ K ) ) <> ( 0. K ) & ( ( ( 1_ K ) + ( 1_ K ) ) * ( M1 * (i,i) ) ) = ( 0. K )) by VECTSP_1:def 7,VECTSP_1:def 19;
hence thesis by VECTSP_1:12;
